Laat me de data en de huidige linklogica bekijken om te snappen wat er precies misgaat.

The user is saying the links to the raadsbesluiten (council decisions) don't work yet. Let me look at the current link logic in app.js and the data to understand what's going on.

Looking at the current link logic in `displayResults()`:

```javascript
if (decision.pdf_url) {
    link = decision.pdf_url;
    linkText = 'Bekijk originele PDF →';
} else if (decision.link && decision.link.includes('iBabs')) {
    link = 'https://wassenaar.ibabs.eu/Public/';
    linkText = 'Zoek in iBabs Publieksportaal →';


} else if (decision.link && decision.link.startsWith('http')) {
    link = decision.link;
    linkText = 'Bekijk document →';
}
```

The problem is that `decision.link` contains descriptive text like "Document wassenaar - Bijlage 1. Beleidsnota Ouderenbeleid 2025 - iBabs Publieksportaal" rather than an actual URL, so the iBabs check matches but just links to the generic portal instead of the specific document.

I need to examine the actual data structure to see what link information is really available.
